            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "What about IBM Plex Sans? It differentiates lower-case L and upper-case I even more:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1264\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-02-19 at 11 41 07 AM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/38269494/108559134-66848d80-72a7-11eb-91c3-5bcb1dce19fb.png\">\r\n\r\nTo use one of the many Google Fonts, we could either:\r\n1. Link in the HTML `<head>` (the below code is copied straight from the Google Fonts page):\r\n    ```\r\n    <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.gstatic.com\">\r\n    <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=IBM+Plex+Sans:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400;1,700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n2. Download the font and serve it.\r\n\r\nIn either case we don't have to bank on folks having the font installed locally, I think.",
