        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I made a branch [`docs-fonts-serve`](https://github.com/GenericMappingTools/pygmt/tree/docs-fonts-serve) which demos what serving a font would be like. @seisman I guess we can't preview unless I turn it into a PR?\r\n\r\nThis setup does not use Google. IBM Plex Sans is licensed under [OFL](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SIL_Open_Font_License), meaning it's free to use and serve etc. Many fonts fall into this category. Font files are about 300 KB in total so not much of an impact on repo size I think. Serving the font guarantees that all users see the same thing (I think).\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1266\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-02-19 at 1 04 58 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/38269494/108567099-08aa7280-72b4-11eb-9cfb-f39061436e85.png\">\r\n\r\nI think this looks pretty nice, but I'm a bit of an aesthete...",
